<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-12-24T20:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-12-24T20:29:00-05:00" n="69" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d69">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">837.73/27: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Long</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-12-24T20:00:00-05:29"><hi rend="italic">December 24,
                                        1920—8 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received December 25—5:35
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>360. This Legation is informed that suspension of the Western Union
                            Telegraph Company’s permit to land at Cojimar was ordered by President
                            Menocal to-day.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Long</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>